## Best Settings for an Elongated Cushion Cut Ring

The setting requirements for an elongated cushion cut ring differ from standard cushion settings in one critical dimension: the prong head must accommodate the elongated outline of the stone. A standard cushion solitaire setting is typically sized for 1.00–1.08 L/W ratio stones; placing a 1.20 L/W elongated cushion in a head designed for a square stone produces misaligned prongs and incorrect corner coverage. Buyers must either select settings explicitly designed for elongated stones or verify with the jeweler that the setting head can accommodate the specific L/W ratio of their diamond.

At Blue Nile, the 4-prong solitaire settings are the most accommodating of elongated cushions because their open prong architecture is least constrained by a specific stone outline. The [Petite Solitaire 14K White Gold at $1,000](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/petite-solitaire-engagement-ring-item-194386?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) and the [Classic Four Prong Solitaire Platinum at $1,180](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/classic-four-prong-solitaire-engagement-ring-item-194156?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) can both be ordered in elongated cushion head sizes — buyers should specify the stone's L/W ratio when ordering to ensure the correct head size is used, which is a standard customization at Blue Nile, not an exception.

Pavé band settings pair well with elongated cushions because the sparkle distribution along the band complements the elongated stone's directional geometry — both the stone and the ring produce light along the same axis as the finger. The [Riviera Pavé 14K White Gold at $1,515](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/riviera-pave-engagement-ring-item-195326?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (390 reviews) is the most popular pavé band option and works effectively with elongated cushions for buyers who want shoulder sparkle that reinforces the elongated axis of the ring. The twisted pavé band is particularly strong with elongated cushions — the [Petite Twist Diamond 14K Rose Gold at $1,380](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/petite-twist-diamond-engagement-ring-item-195538?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (417 reviews) adds organic movement that contrasts the elongated cushion's structured rectangular outline in a way many buyers find more interesting than a plain band.

> "Elongated cushion cuts need more careful setting attention than round or square cushions. The head size and prong placement must match the stone's actual length-to-width ratio — not a generic cushion head. Buyers who skip this verification step end up with prongs that either don't cover the corners correctly or crowd the stone's table area. Always confirm the head dimensions match your stone before the setting is ordered."
> — Farzana, Diamond Consultant

