## Elongated Cushion Cut Ring in Yellow Gold

Yellow gold is the historically authentic metal for cushion-style diamonds — the cushion's ancestor, the old mine cut, was set in yellow gold in Victorian and Edwardian pieces, and the elongated variant reads as most historically coherent in yellow gold. In {{year}}, yellow gold has seen resurgent demand in the elongated cushion format because the combination produces a vintage-inspired aesthetic the current market values: an elongated fancy shape in warm metal reads as deliberately timeless rather than trend-forward.

Yellow gold neutralizes warmth in H-I color elongated cushions more aggressively than any other metal — it's the strongest color neutralizer available. Elongated cushions already permit lower color grades to read acceptably, because their larger face-up table distributes any body color across a larger surface; in yellow gold, an I color elongated cushion can read acceptably warm against the metal, which opens budget by permitting one or two color grade relaxations without visible quality loss. The [Petite Split Shank Solitaire 14K Yellow Gold at $1,165](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/petite-split-shank-solitaire-engagement-ring-item-192982?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the entry yellow gold setting for elongated cushions.

